New layer

new_layer.Rd

Create a new Layer object.

new_layer(source, current, total, units)

Arguments

source

character file path for the underlying data.
current

numeric current proportion of values held in existing conservation areas (e.g. 0.1 = 10%).
total

numeric total amount of all values in the underlying data.
units

character units for the values in the underlying data.

Value

A Layer object.

Examples

# create new object
l <- new_layer(source = tempfile(), current = 0.1, total = 12, units = "ha")

# print object
print(l)
